President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his administration. John Rakolta, Jr. of Michigan is nominated to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the United Arab Emirates. Kyle McCarter of Illinois is nominated to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Kenya. Mark Rosen of Connecticut is nominated to be the United States Executive Director of the International Monetary Fund. Additionally, President Trump has announced his intent to appoint David F. Eisner of New York as an Assistant Secretary of the Treasury for Management.